The '''2011 Liga Primer Indonesia''' is the inaugural and only season of [[Liga Primer Indonesia]], an [[Indonesia]]n professional [[Association football|football]] league.<ref>[http://bolaindo.com/?page=berita&sub=detail&id=14554 Liga Primer Indonesia Diluncurkan]</ref><ref>[http://ligaprimerindonesia.co.id/news/headline29.html Wujudkan komitmen menuju sepakbola mandiri dan profesional]</ref> It began on 8 January 2011<ref name="Jadwal LPI">{{cite web|title=Inilah Jadwal Kompetisi LPI 2011|url=http://www.beritajatim.com/detailnews.php/5/Olahraga/2011-01-12/89635/Inilah_Jadwal_Kompetisi_LPI_2011|publisher=Beritajatim.com|date=12 January 2011 |accessdate=31 January 2011|language=Indonesian}}</ref> and will end in 20 November 2011.<ref name="Jadwal LPI">{{cite web|title=Inilah Jadwal Kompetisi LPI 2011|url=http://www.beritajatim.com/detailnews.php/5/Olahraga/2011-01-12/89635/Inilah_Jadwal_Kompetisi_LPI_2011|publisher=Beritajatim.com|date=12 January 2011 |accessdate=31 January 2011|language=Indonesian}}</ref>

==Teams==
The inaugural season begun with 19 teams, four of the 19 were defected from [[PSSI]] sanctioned league of whom three ([[PSM Makassar]], [[Persema Malang]] and [[Persibo Bojonegoro]]) defected from the top tier [[Indonesia Super League]], and [[Persebaya]] from the second tier [[Liga Indonesia Premier Division]].

